<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kair</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok, wondering what level a group would need to be to take down the plasmatic priest to complete the first step of the cleric epic?<P>One group of six.<P>Tactics?  Things you've learned by doing and helping?<P>Thanks!<BR>Kair<BR>Bristlebane Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dystopya</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Probably 1 group of 55 plus. Shrug. Maybe less.<P>Pretty easy fight really. Just find out where he spawns, then determine what your path will be to zone in... Go back, turn items in, hit DA, run to zone in via predetermined path.<P>Make sure you have a chanter there to mez any adds that may have been pissed off by his AE nukage. He cheals, so lots of stuns help.<P>Have fun.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You could probably do it with 1 group of 6, but he will CH.<P>There are a lot of things you can do, but what seems to work pretty well is to wait for the right seeker to pop, then have a melee class that knows the route to the zone, tag him and run and out of the zone when the priest is at the zone line.<P>Have another person designated to hail him (with "what plasmatic priest") to keep him at the zone line until the melee zones back in.  Then give him the statue and wack him.<P>Might be safer to bring 2 groups.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>60th Dwarven High Priest<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kair</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks!!  I appreciate the advice!<P>Kair<BR>Bristlebane Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cali</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">For my slaying of the plasmatic priest I had: 59 Shaman, 54 Warrior, 54 Druid and myself 54 Cleric.<P>I went in.  Found his spawn point. Walked the path several times.  Buffed, medded to full and went to him.  Stunned him (no damage = no summoning) hit my DA and ran my butt to the zone.  The group hailed him repeatedly to keep him in zone in.<P>I zoned back in, handed my item and started stunning him.  Only fear was that he would walk or summon us into the zone so we played pull the priest away from the zone while keeping him from CHing. LOL! But he died pretty easy.<P>What I found amusing was that before we could take mine out there were at least 3 groups there to take out one for another cleric.  *giggles*  So we went and killed Fire Giants in Sol B.  <P>(Shaman rock!)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jerricoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">1 group of 55+ can easily do it. He's a gimp and with a couple of high level tanks he should be a push over for you.<P>DA works, I gate pulled him to the zone with no probems also.<P>------------------<BR>Jerricoe Seer<BR>High Priest<BR><A HREF="http://www.redskyeq.com" TARGET=_blank>Red Sky</A> - Bertoxxulous - <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15665" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sollwin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">We took him in his room with a single group, 52 and up.<P>------------------<BR>Sollwin Lifestar<BR>58th Halfling Templar of Bristlebane<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=41743" TARGET=_blank>Inspect Me!</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cyzia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">All 3 times, we killed him in his room. Only 1 CH. All people lvl 55+.<P>------------------<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5722" TARGET=_blank>Cyzia</A></B><P><I>Templar of Tunare</I><P><B>Cazic-Thule Server</B></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">nonnuss</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heh, killed him last night with a 60 mage epic pet.  I CH'd the pet once was easy =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Windeliane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">We rushed him in his room, with 3 groups 45-55 lol, i wasn't sure what was needed. Took 5 seconds, chain stuning, not even a heal needed  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Good luck !!<BR><P>------------------<BR>Windeliane<BR>Healer of the 58th circle<BR>Member of L'Ordre du Phoenix on Terris-Thule</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Qienn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When I did it a while back I was a 51 cleric. Had a 54 mage, 48 druid, 51 ranger. Everyone was oom except I had 40m after the fight.<P>I pulled the priest to the zone (make sure you know the way). I didnt even cast DA and high tailed it off the ledge back to the zone.<P>He CHed on us once if I remember right, but over all he is a wuss. I would recommend more people for this, but 3 others was all I could muster at 4 am  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>Good luck with it,<BR>Qienn</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Throckjr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">51 Cleric, 55 SK, 55 Mage w/ air pet? the one that stuns, and 53 shaman.<P>Pulled ala Dalur's post - just have someone run point and get the doors open for your puller.  He'll run solo to the zone, and the plasmatic preist will spawn right where the seeker dies.<P>The walkthrough is WAY OFF - BEFORE the mage land Malo I was stunning the guy and doing it with Sound of Force AND Holy Might, so either I was WAY lucky or this guy does NOT have much MR and is DEFINITELY NOT impervious to stun.<P>This is only hard if you don't pay attention to what you're doing.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kair</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wow!  Thanks for all the great tips!<P>I think I'm gonna get to 51 before trying this, but I know I have several low 50's and a few high 50's to help me with this.  I'm glad that so many people found it relatively simple with only one group of people.<P>Thanks for all the helpful hints to about pulling!<P>Kair<BR>Bristlbane Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lyli</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I killed the priest with 2 groups, average level was around 51 but we had a 58 monk with us. It was a bit of overkill but I figured better safe than sorry.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I handed the item to him, he attacked me, and I hauled arse back to the zone in. Make sure you have the right "a seeker" too, I almost handed the item to the wrong one. :P<P>Lyli Moonwatyr<BR>57th Templar of Tunare<BR>Order of the Jade Dragon ~ Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Me (50 cleric), 60 tank, 56 rogue. Walked the route a few times to get it down. Popped DA, handed in statue, ran to zone, tank popped defensive and went to town. Rogue stepped in at about 80h. Seeker CHealed, turned on rogue (ouch-she dropped FAST) and left me and tank with me at 60m. Tank kept working on him, I kept him healed, tank died, seeker summoned me...then turned and started walking away-CLERIC MELEE POWER!!! I popped off my last couple charges of my Oil of Fennin Ro, burned my last bit of mana on a couple of resisted sounds of force and finished him off the old school way, including a quick cast of Extinguish Fatigue about half-way through. WOOT! Never so glad I bought the Iksar Berserker Club a couple of days before. So yeah, a single group should be able to take him pretty easy, especially if you have a second cleric or enchanter along (so someone can chain stun and prevent a CHeal).<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 52nd Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) Master Tailor (161)<BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
